    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Werth's article on the development and use of human growth hormone is a succinct indictment of the most troubling aspects of America's health-care system. Why do insurance companies subsidize human growth hormone shots while they desperately seek to avoid paying for "experimental" drugs that might ease the pain of thousands of Americans with AIDS? Health care through market research may be the death of us yet. JOHN T. O'KEEFE Cambridge, Mass</p>
      </block>
